Partly sunny- med. wind- 1.5" rain last 3 days
Med. wind from se- sunny- 1.1" rain yesterday.
Channel froze 12/4- ice around edge of lake 12/8- frozen completely 12/28
Sunny- light wind- algae seems to be increasing
2" of rain yesterday- low evg. temps increasing clarity
Winds calm- sunny- last August- Secchi was 3.75 ft.
Wind northwest and the weather is sunny.
Wind northeast and the sky is cloudy.   Enjoyed newsletter!
Lake level is 16" above normal- wind is southwest- partly cloudy- heavy rain has raised lake daily with most piers are underwater- many have floated away.  Lake level: very high
Wind northeast and sunny.  Missed reading last week because of rain and more rain.
Last reading.  Water level: 9" above normal
Lots of rain this past week.
No rain for about 2 weeks so the lake level is quite low.
Sunny day with a light northwest wind.
Department of Natural Resources removed about 10-000 carp this past week- and lake level is down approximately 22" from fall 1986.
Rained approximately 4.5" since 7/3/1987 and the lake has risen about 7"-8".
Lots of rain in the past 10 days.
Opening day-fishing- lots of activity of lake- nice weather
Warm- sunny day- slight wind from southwest.
Overcast- lots of algae- fishing not too good
Clear sunny day- quite a bit of algae
Partly cloudy- light wind- quite a bit of algae near shore
Quite a bit of algae near shore depending on the wind direction.
Algae is clearing up as water is getting cooler; swimming and water activities seem to be ending; people are starting to take out their piers; fishing hasn't been good
Too cold for swimming slight algae level reading is slightly better than last year at this time
Clear bright day-- last reading for 1989; too cold for swimming
Overcast- taken with john Wilson- will be taking over
Brown water due to run-off following heavy rains.
LAC LA BELLE - AMBIENT LAKE MONITORING
Temperature is 80 degrees F- some murkiness- and strong wind out of the southeast.
DEEP HOLE AT 45FT- INTREGRATED WATER COLUMN
hot - finally some rain last night - 3/4"   Wind 10 mph
Warm sunny evening.  Slight breeze- a few scattered motorboats- kayaks- and children's sailboats.
Sunny day- my kayak was the only boat on the lake
Sunny with a reddish haze. Lake has been quiet for days.  Now only 2 fishing boats and 2 kayaks
Overcast-no boats but my kayak- ripples on water
Part sunny- part cloudy- wind 5 mph
Bright overcast sky and little lake traffic
Calm- sunny one day after rain- wind and hail storm

column1: oxygen sample for 30 feet was white flock!  only took 1 mini drop to change the blue indicator to clear.  Had photographer from "Living on the Lake" magazine with me - doing article on volunteer monitors.

column2: sunny - air 80'- wind 5 mph - beautiful day!  Nights have been cool - 55'
Sunny and calm with one motor boat zooming.  No rain in several days.

column1: Lots of gulls- geese on the lake - people are complaining.  Not much in the way of zebra mussels - very small ones on the corners of our pier- but certainly not encrusting the pontoons like other years.

column2: it has been very cold lately- and very windy. finally got a day with little wind and a little warmer - 41'F  The lake is high- and a green/brown color.

column1: my temp guage wasn't working- so I did the DO without the temp because this may be my only window of opportunity for a while.  I'll do it again when I can- and when I can get temp guage working.

column2: Calm- patchy clouds- 83' air - sailing school has started.

column1: interesting to see the doop hole is often a foot or so clearer than the NW basin

column2: Sunny- lots of boat traffic the day before.
patchy clouds- air 75' F   1" of rain yesterday -  wind 5 mph
Heavy rain the day before 1.87 inches measured in Oconomowoc

column1: 10 inches of rain in last 2 1/2 weeks - the lake is very high and lost of stuff floating around - duckweed- branches- etc. perfect day - sunny- calm - 10" of rain in last few weeks - lake is very high perfect day - sunny- calm- 70' air 10 inches of rain in last 2 1/2 weeks - the lake is very high and lost of stuff floating around - duckweed- branches- ect. perfet day - sunny- calm - 10" of rain in last few weeks - lake is very high

column2: Sunny- no boats- several days of no rain.
Sunny- Warm and Calm - a perfet day for my first paddle

column1: the new DO meter is WONDERFUL - thank you!!!
I was accompanied by a few seagulls- tow geese- and a solitary loon.
Last week 4 loons cruised by- also saw a small flock of Red breasted mergansers- maybe 20 ruddy ducks- and some scaups.

column2: Sunny- Passing Clouds-  Air 80'F- Wind 8 mph  lake has brownish cast to it

column1: After all this rain - 9" in two weeks the lake is the highest since we moved here in 1971
Our pier is on the land - we put it in nad a week later it floated back out.

column2: Sunny- lake green with suspended small green particles
sunny- goooey algae clumps seen on yellow green lake
Wind 12 MPH  overcast with sun peeking out

column1: the lake is finally returning to normal levels - still a little high.  got the pier back in  Yesterday - that makes 3 round trips so far this summer.
cool nights- no rain
nights have been cool - in the 50's- not much rain
lots of gulls- a few trees just starting to turn colors Sunny- Calm- beautiful  Air 75'F
nights have been cool - in the 50's- not much rain
lots of gulls- a few trees just starting to turn colors

column2: cool- grey day - dead calm -  air 55'F-  Clouds reflected in the water- white feathers  floating- wild gees in long v's overhead- and scarlet maples among the russet of oaks - a stunning day - I'm grateful for an excuse to go paddling.

column1: my companions today were 4 loons- 3 grebes- a goldeneye- and a pack of gulls.

column2: Perfect day!! 70'F air- sunny calm - families out tubing- sailboats trying to race
sunny- passing clouds-   wind 2 mph  air 75'F
Calm quiet.  Saw great blue heron and red shoulder hawk on the way back
Sunny with slight breese and small waves
sunny- calm- air 75'F   algae bloom at shoreline-  Monarch popped out of the chrysalis on the Marsh Milkweed.

Windy- waves 2-8 inches at site (less in my cove). No boats- the only one fishing was a kingfisher.   Rained in the morning and more is expected in the afternoon. My first use of my new- improved secchi disk.  It went straight down despite the current and wind. Yeah!
Sunny- a few clouds and ripples on the water.  Ocassionally speed boats.
A few waves- no clouds.  Beautiful day.
calm sunny beautiful - air 78 - nights have been cool
Sunny- one other boat on the lake
cold paddling- sunny-  wind 5 mph  lots of gull-  3 coots
Sunny- calm and quiet.  Just me and a solo cormorant
Disturbed on comorant and 2 drake mallards. One boat passed slowly.  The rest of the lake was quiet and calm.
calm- overcast - some sun peeking through - swallows cruising the lake
Sunny with a light breeze.  Sailboats and a few motor boats
A few days after VERY heavy rains made the lake silty-
hot- hazy- light wind-  the water here is clearer than the NW basin

lake was dead calm - cold- but sunny - the first paddle of the year felt great. Accompanied by 2 terns- 2 gulls- 2 swallows- 6 red-breasted mergansers and one powerboat joyriding up and down the length of the lake 4 times.
calm- hazy- a few fishermen out there  lake looks clearer than April  Air 75'
Beautiful calm day.  Sailboat races waiting for wind.
light wind- sunny- air 65'F-  nights have been cool
Beautiful day- earlier it was sunny and busy. Now- calm- 1 speed boat and two human powered boats shared thhe lake.
Calm-  just me-  two water skiers- one garfish and a zillion japenese beetles floating in the lake + buzzing my hat.  Hots days and nights - air 90'F
Heavy rains last night. Lake very calm. Only 2 people on the lake- me on my kayak and a young woman playing with a dog.
Quiet lake with a light breese- small waves and a a few boats fishing
Most of the motor  boats are gone from the lake.  Its been fairly quiet here for days and the water is very clear
sunny- air 70'F wind 7 mph  trees are changing - perfect fall day
Deep green wave covered lake.  Only other on it were a goose pair who scolded me.
Sunny- Calm- air 67"f beautiful - Just me and one loon

column1: disappointing to see lake so green this early in the year

column2: overcast - bright  air 80'F  no significant rain for a while - the lawn is crispy
Lake was calm and quiet only one female duck with her duckling.  Water very low- green- and nice.

column1: lake is low - we need rain!!!!
but despite the hot days- no shoreline algae blooms-  no rain= no runoff

column2: Sunny- Calm- air 78'F  Opti regatta hoping for wind.  Still not much rain-  nights are getting cooler at last
Sunny- clear-  Air 60'F- wind 0-3 mph-   lots of gulls- a seaplane- and me

column1: Last night was 44'F

column2: sunny- clear sky- Air 55'-  Wind 3 mph

column1: Honking geese - talking about warmer destinations'
Algae bloom right at shoreline - lots of dead leaves there

column2: Calm- sunny- beautiful paddling day The lake looks clearer at the deep hole than in the nw basin- where farm runoff is still and issue.
flat calm- sunny- Water amazingly clear today - last night was cool - 50'f   68'F now
more millfoil this year to surface - weekend boating means lots of floaters. y

column1: Weather dead calm.- hot sunny.
we had a raft of about 50 white pelicans show up july 29th - i got pictures!

column2: sunny-  wind 5 mph-  air 68'F-   beautiful paddling!!  saw family of 3 grebes on the way out.
Flat calm- air is 75'F- lots of gulls on the lake
Warm!!  78'F-  sunny  wind 2 mph   2 1/2 inches of rain last Sunday night.  Jet ski going in tight circles

column1: Just learned a commercial fisherman got 28-000 lbs of carp and buffalo last winter. remote controlled submarine pulling nets under the ice? whoa
Also a new settling pond for farm runoff from golf course creek.
The wind came up whwile I was out there - tried a bucket for a sea anchor - it worked pretty well.
A big mayfly hatch this year - their bodies are floating on the water. - don't remember ever seeing so many.

Also - if the phosphorus sample is weird- it might be because I forgot to bring the water collection bottle out- and had paddled out 40 minutes with no time to go get it- so I used my iced tea naugaline bottle. dumped the tea and rinsed it virgorously 10 times.  I hope this worked.

column2: Air 68'F- Wind very light-  algae bloom at shoreline-  raft of 20+ coots near deep hole
Wind calm - overcast- but bright-   Air 55 F-

column1: Just me an a few swallows.

column2: Air 70'F- wind 3 mph  sunny- clear-  beautiful day - lots of motorboats- tubers and skiers

column1: A little bouncy for my kayak
lots of minnows along our shoreline-  my water sample had little guys swimming around in it - daphnia- I think

column2: sunny- air 75F - light wind-  beaujtifully quiet after a busy weekend
light wind- sunny- quiet!!  Air 60'F  leaves just starting to turn

column1: gull feathers all over the place.  There has been the usual huge gathering of gulls on the lake in the fall. Must be a at least 300

column2: beautiful- very warm day/. Air 78'F  wind calm-. on the lake with a loon- a few gulls- and one waterskier.
air 68'F- clouds come and go- quiet lake- wind 3 mph
perfect summer day---  Calm- sunny- air 80'F

column1: except there is a nasty algae bloom along our shore - would not consider swimming

column2: Sunny- air 76"F- wind light- algae bloom getting started on our shoreline. We have seen this too much this summer.

column1: Nights have been cool- in the 60's- days in the 80's  -   not much rain lately.

column2: Flat calm- Air 68" night was cool - 55'F  lots of gull feathers floating on surface.  Just me- two skiers- and a grebe.
calm- air 55'F- cold nights- occaisional carp surfacing and splashing as I paddle past.
calm- air 55'F- cold nights- occasional carp surfacing and splashing as I paddle past.
sunny- wind 4mph  air 73'F Lots of rain last two days-

Clear- sunny skies.  Cool night temps in preceding days.  26* C / 78* F air temp.  Winds 080 at 10 kts or ~ 12 mph.  Lake was busy with traffic varying from paddle boarders- kayakers and sail boats to pontoon and speed boats pulling skiers.  Wore no sunglasses.  Jet ski

Mostly clear- sunny skies cleared from morning thunderstorms. Flooding and storms the night before- received 4.6" rain NWS.  70* F night temps.  27* C  air temp. Winds 240 at 14 kts. Lake was not busy.  Wore no sunglasses. Jet ski

Overcast skies. Record rains in preceding days. 27* C / 81* F air temp. Winds calm.  Light traffic on lake.  Wore no sunglasses. Pontoon boat. With Lisa Conley. Overcast skies. Record rains in preceding days. 27* C / 81* F air temp. Winds calm.  Light traffic on lake.  Wore no sunglasses. Pontoon boat. With Lisa Conley.
calm- overcast- air temp 80'F-  lots of boating- lots of rain- storms lately
Clear- sunny skies. 76* F air temp. Winds 070 at 8 kts.  Lake was moderately busy with traffic varying from kayakers and sail boats to pontoon and speed boats.  Wore no sunglasses. Jet ski

column1: nasty algae bloom on our shore - NW end of lake.  looks like Pea soup with milk spilled in it and smells awful.
Calm- Sunny- air 80"F
nasty algae bloom on our shore - NW end of lake.  looks like Pea soup with milk spilled in it and smells awful.
Looks like we are having Turnover

column2: bright- overcast- cool nights- 83F- no wind
calm- bright/overcast Air 83'F  nights have been cool - in the 60's

column1: pea soup algae on our shore
problem last week with runoff from golf course reconstruction erosion controls. I have pictures
some carp surfacing as I paddled
Cottonwood fluff floating around
Interesting that I got a reading of 8.5 at the SE ( city ) basin-  7.0 at the deep hole- and 5.0 at the NW end.  Calm- Sunny- Air 78 F
some carp surfacing as I paddled
Cottonwood fluff floating around
Interesting that I got a reading of 8.5 at the SE ( city ) basin-  7.0 at the deep hole- and 5.0 at the NW end.

column2: sunny- 75 degrees- light breeze. Lots of boating during this 4th of July week.
78 F- slight breeze- sun/no clouds with slight haze- algae notes at my shoreline
82F- cloudy to partly sunny- slight breeze- some algae visible along west shore of the lake. Its been dry and warm in the past week.

The second of two significant rain events totally 7-8 inches occurred yesterday. Today is sunny and calm with warm temperature. The golf course construction on the north side of LLB continues and the loose soil and water breached the silt fence and ran south to the lake. Significant amounts of muddy water ran in from the golf course creek and the drains  in personal lots. There were many complaints. I can hear and see the construction truck attempting to move mud away from the silt fence and also move dirt into some type of a dike formation.

Sunny- 80F-slight breeze. Significant rain events on Aug 17- 20- 26-27. Golf course construction underway with much loose soil. The rain events caused significant amounts of soil to wash into the lake on the NW side of LLB. As of today there is still standing muddy water between my house and the future golf course.

79F almost no breeze; Slow No Wake rule still in force due to high water. No rain in the past 7 days but the lake level has not gone down yet. Significant bright green algae along the north shoreline and covering our swimming area.
Sunny- 79F- breezy; cold front and more rain coming. Slow No Wake determination removed Sept 23rd because lake level has been going down although it is still at above normal level.

75F- breezy- mostly sunny. bright green algae on NW shoreline. Lake level rising again due to rains and saturated ground. 75F- breezy- mostly sunny. bright green algae on NW shore. Golf course construction on-going- as are the rains and run off into the lake.
partly sunny- light breeze. 67 F. First reading of the season. Spring has been cool- rainy and cloudy.

Sunny with some wispy clouds- light SW breeze- 68F. Lake water appears to be somewhat dirty (suspended sediment) at my shoreline on the NW corner of the lake. Yesterday we had strong SW winds all day and 2 thunderstorms passed through over night. Cottonwood dust blew around and landed on our screens.
The cool and windy spring continues. Lake temps today were a bit lower the 2 weeks ago for the upper surface waters. One result of this is less boating activity on the lake.

Past week was rainy - approx 3" at our shore--and there was a significant muddy water runoff for over 4 hours from the golf course construction project on June 30th.  Tomorrow is 4th of July; boating is picking up today and will be very busy for the holiday weekend.

column1: Secchi reading at the city end of the lake was 7.5"

column2: In the midst of the hottest week of 2019. It's been dry for 10 days. Today sunny- light breeze- 82F. Water along my shoreline is murkier than past summers but there is no algae on the surface. I've seen 3 monarch butterflies so far.
We've had less rain than normal for the past 2-3 weeks. At our pier ladder the water level is down a couple of inches.

At my shoreline I see that the water is more clear than anytime this summer and the water level is down at least 2". We've had less rain in recent weeks. Rain is again in the forecast for the upcoming week. I can see algae but no large algae blooms today or anytime this summer at our shore.
Perfect weather  70F- no to slight breeze- clear sky. Very few boats on the lake. Nights have been cool.

Feels like summer today at 11AM. 75F- no breeze and full sun. However- like September- the lake was very quiet and there was significant algae at my shore as well as visible from the boat in the middle of the lake.

Breezy- sunny and clear sky- 62F. The lake looks notably green in color all along my shoreline- pier and out on the open water. Saw 40 small ducks swimming together; dark heads and grey bodies. Didn't know their identify.

Spring-like morning. 62 F with hazy sun and a NE breeze. The breeze on the lake feels like an air conditioner is blowing right at me. Noticed first mosquitos today. Baltimore orioles have been at the feeder for 2 weeks.
Sunny morning- light SE breeze- upper 70sF -- Tropic storm Cristobal impact forecasted for S Wi this evening. Phlox + lilacs bloomed within the past week.
Sunny- NW breeze- 68F- rained last night-

Monday after long 4th of July weekend. Yesterday was satellite date but the lake was too busy for monitoring. Weather has been hot. Today is sunny- 79F with light SW breeze. Some algae visible along my NW shoreline this morning.
Sunny 80F- breezy-" lake smells like smoke" from my 6 year old assistant
Sunny 78F light breeze. The warm and relatively dry summer continues. My lakeshore remains free from visible algae growths.

76F and sunny. Weather continues to be summery with the majority of the days in the 80s. Rainfall is below. Secchi reading in the SE basin was 5.5' (taken out of curiosity).  The monarchs and swallow tail butterflies are busy with the yellow coneflowers and joe pye weed.
Quiet labor day yesterday. weather cooled down.
68F- light breezy- skies are hazy with tint of yellow/orange due to west coast forest fire smoke that is carried here by the winds.

Wonderful weather for SWIMS work. Sunny- no wind- 71F and midweek so few boats.  Unfortunately- green algae visible from my pier on the NNW shoreline. First day of fall was yesterday. Asters still blooming but yellow coneflowers are about done.
